cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.ME, cs.ROB, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about robots built from cable-driven tensegrity structures and their design and control. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the static equilibrium model and optimization problem for controlling the tension forces in the cables of the robots. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with the mechanics of tensegrity structures and their application in robots. 
- cs.ROB (Robotics and Perception) is another possible category as the paper focuses on the design and control of robots. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a computational method for solving the inverse statics problem in compound tensegrity robots.
